    "The power of our statistical test, aiming to avoid a Type II error, was calculated using a two-sample t-test with an alpha (α) level of 0.05 63.",
    "Next, for entities tagged as both EC and ENC, due to potential opposing evidence trends for carcinogenecity, going forth called as 'Disputed' entities, we wanted to provide probabilistic inference based on evidence trends.",
    "Thus, our total of 554 'Disputed' carcinogenic entities were subject to Bayesian temporal Probabilistic Carcinogenic Denomination (PCarD) to assign likelihood for carcinogenic 'Nominee' status relative to changes in evidence sentiment over time.",
    "(Details 'Disputed' entities are cataloged in Supplementary Data 3 -spTable3.xlsx)",
    "The observed counts of entity 𝑌 𝑖, including both EC and ENC counts, as a function of elapsed time interval 𝑡 𝑖 was modeled using a Negative Binomial distribution to accommodate overdispersion observed in the data:"
  ],
